We cannot here do more thanindicate the salient points in Tertullian's Christology. The Son of Goel, the Word, is not a mere attribute of the Father, such as His wisdom or poucr3 His generation is before the creation of the world. His Sonship is threefold: the Word eternally in God¹; the Second Person coming forth in the act of creation ; the Son become Man, a visible Personality over against God2.
